3e812658-f116-4e98-9a52-1cd484f747c6.do_description: To make the output, you have to...complete a line with the colors. If it's red, fill the line in until you hit the gray bar. If it's blue, fill in until you hit the bottom or top edge.
3e812658-f116-4e98-9a52-1cd484f747c6.grid_description: The output grid size...stays the same
3e812658-f116-4e98-9a52-1cd484f747c6.see_description: In the input, you should see...a square with a gray line and blue and red tiles

605e15b6-6699-427a-b3a2-8586e684d090.do_description: To make the output, you have to...look to see if there is an even amount of colored tiles. If so, then the blue tiles always go up and the red tiles always go down. You must complete a line as far as it will go. If there are three tiles, then blue goes down and red goes up. If there are five tiles, then red goes up and blue goes down.
605e15b6-6699-427a-b3a2-8586e684d090.see_description: In the input, you should see...a black grid with red and blue tiles.

9d13c5d6-62c0-4e2c-9034-8bb6a2abf047.do_description: To make the output, you have to...extend the right blue tiles downward and the red tiles need to connect.
9d13c5d6-62c0-4e2c-9034-8bb6a2abf047.see_description: In the input, you should see...a black grid with red and blue tiles.

9df134c9-ed4e-452f-bc3a-cbb92af1e414.do_description: To make the output, you have to... look at whether the number of tiles of each color is even or not. So if there are 2 red tiles, then red is even. If a color is even, then you must color each of the tiles under the colored tile to the bottom of the grid with the same color. If a color is not even, then you must color each of the tiles above the colored tile to the top of the grid with the same color. Repeat for each color.
9df134c9-ed4e-452f-bc3a-cbb92af1e414.grid_description: The output grid size... is the same as the input grid
9df134c9-ed4e-452f-bc3a-cbb92af1e414.see_description: In the input, you should see... a 5x10 grid with red and blue tiles
